- glutDisplayFunc(my_function)
    - My_function contains instructions for redrawing the scene
- glutKeyboardFunc(keyboard)
    - keyboard() is a function for handling keyboard events
    - It recieves the keys pressed
- vec2 is a 2D vector
- glutKeyboardFunc takes a callback function which is run whenever a keyboard event is fired
- GLuint returns an unsigned integer
    - Execution will be performed on the gpu
- radiosity: enegry based approach of ray tracing (very very slow)
- Ray tracing must have the whole database availible at all times
- Practical approach of lighting:
    - Process objects one at a time in the order they are generated by the application
    - Consider only local ligthing
